description:
The incumbent will response to handle customer enquiries, and perform sales & marketing, sales operations related matters.

Requirements:

Degree holders or Form 6 or above
2 years or above working experiences in customer service, preferably in property industries;
Team player with pleasant, proactive and customer-oriented attitude;
Good command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;

Candidates with more experience will be considered as Sales Supervisor.


Benefits:
We offer competitive remuneration package including annual leave, discretionary bonus, dental and medical coverage and Top-up MPF. We value our employees’ career development and provide them with a variety of internal and external training opportunities.

Application Methods:

Online application – Visit our website http://www.hkri.com (Career Opportunities/HKR International Limited) to complete the online application form;
Email – Send your detailed resume and expected salary to "Apply Now";
Whatsapp – 6845 7015;
Fax – 2902 2510
Applicants not invited for interview within two months may consider their applications unsuccessful. All information will be used solely for recruitment purpose and will be destroyed when the recruitment process is finished. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with the employer’s personal data policies, a copy of which will be provided upon request.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for marketing of properties, support and execute a full spectrum of branding, marketing and promotional campaigns;
Handle media and advertisement planning and execution across a wide platform, such as sales brochure, TV, outdoor billboards, print advertisements in different newspapers; & magazines, online media and various marketing collaterals etc.;
Conduct market research and analysis;
Champion project implementation, including preparation of project plan, progress management, budgetary control and ensure seamless communication between different stakeholders.

Requirements:

University graduate in Marketing, Surveying or related disciplines;
5+ years Sales & Marketing experience in Hong Kong property related field;
Sound knowledge and experience in Marketing, Advertising and PR for property sales projects;
Strong in market research, product planning and development, and marketing strategy formulation and implementation;
Knowledge on Residential (First-hand Sales) Ordinance
Excellent communication and interpersonal Skills;
Excellent command of both spoken and written English & Chinese/Mandarin;
Self-motivated, independent, responsible and flexible; willing to work overtime and during holidays.

